race.comment: Tough race with a host of these close to wins and several trialling well for their first outing. BARDIGRUB (7) has been runner-up last two and looks tough to beat. Led and just missed last time making it back-to-back near misses. Tricky draw to overcome here but has good pace and will take catching. SICILIAN PRINCESS (12) is another who has strung together multiple placings. Finished a safely held second fresh behind the ultra impressive Bassett Babe who is engaged in the previous race. Fitter and can measure up this time. RATHLIN EXPRESS (3) was beaten half a length behind Gaza on the main track latest and narrowly beaten there the start prior too. One of the leading chances. RAMASIS (2) debuts off of two trial wins. Barrier 1 also of huge benefit for a debutant.
